				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">newly 50 bard advice<a name="63969"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 23 04 10:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Heya. I'm a soon to ding 50 bard on Morden Rasp (Zorath if you wanna look me up). Just wanted some advice/suggestions on what direction to take.
<br />

<br />
- <u>Levels vs. AAs</u>: I wanna hit 70 ASAP, but are there any AAs I should get along the way. Like absolutely required ones that will make leveling go faster.
<br />

<br />
- <u>Best place for money/XP</u>: been farming Rathe Mts. since 38 for decent XP and nice plat. Giants starting to get light blue now. Where is the next place for decent XP but really nice plat.
<br />

<br />
- <u>Required equipment</u>: any extremely useful stuff I should look out for (preferably cheap since this is my first char)? Right now I got a 2.4 drum, full gothic plate, Naraithus (13/21), and Legendary Dagger of Might (13/20).
<br />

<br />
BTW, I'm extremely impressed with bard as a class so far. I usually have my LFG tag on for about 5 minutes before I get a group offer.  In the rare case I dont get a group I can go solo for nice XP. 
<br />

<br />
Other classes have such limited roles/skills, whereas we can do - well almost anything. I could never go back to another class thats for sure. Almost every time I group someone says &quot;wow I didnt know bards could do that&quot;<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
