				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: newly 50 bard advice<a name="64079"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 24 04 1:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree with Lvls &gt; AAs but I have a few exceptions. 
<br />
Get Fading Memories at 63, it costs 12 AAs ad will make your life SO much easier. I also reccommend hitting the AAs for some mana regen right around the same time (level 63) or even sooner if you like to swarm a lot. Get tons of tribute points and use them to boost your mana regen, unless you are doing this trek mostly in groups. 
<br />
   As far as areas to hunt go, I agree with Dulak big time, I'd also encourage you to check out Umbral Plains and Grieg's End for both money and good xp. You can usually find a group pretty fast in GE. You might also solo the rock hoppers and sell the hides, it's big big money and good xp at your level. 
<br />
  Instrument-wise, I'd really encourage you to look at getting some items with mods on them unless you are very close to finishing your epic 1.0, items like Troub's Mace, Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche or Gem Inlaid Longsword are all good ones. Director's Boots, Tear Shaped Ring and Painted Primal Mask are some other items with mods on them. Lleb was right in mentioning the LDoN augs too, but remember that you need the proper slots on your armor to accept an instrument aug, this type of armor is likely LDoN as well so you're looking at a substantial amount of time invested in getting gear with mods. In that amount of time you could probably get your epic  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />
<br />
  Do as much Tak and EF LDoN as you can, the armor, augs and songs from both are essential. 
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
