				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: newly 50 bard advice<a name="64101"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 24 04 2:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A minor warning...if you group with folks higher level than you, especially in LDoN's, you may hit a period from 58 to 62 where you get a little discouraged.
<br />

<br />
The reason is there is kind of a gap in some of our primary songs at these level.
<br />

<br />
ie, If as a 58-61 you group with 5 level 65's in an LDoN (unless your get the 'Ancient' no-drop songs raiding) you will not be able to effectively lull pull or cc mez (and charm will have no use in level appriate groups, and the exp from swarming, if you do so, will be falling off). I would Avoid being the primary puller or cc in HARD LDoN's in this range even if you are all the same level.
<br />

<br />
The recommendations from above seem right on from my experience.
<br />

<br />
Perservere....62-65 is a breeeze, except for aquiring the songs.</span></td>
